us, who uses θυμός\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] instead; once in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; frequently in Eleg. and Lyric poetry and in <i>Ionic dialect</i> and <i>Attic dialect</i> Prose.","strongNumber":"G3709","accentedUnicode":"ὀργή","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3710","matchingForm":"ὀργίζω","stepTransliteration":"orgizō","gloss":"to anger","_zh_tw_Gloss":"生氣","_es_Gloss":"enojar","_zh_Gloss":"生气"},{"strongNumber":"G3711","matchingForm":"ὀργίλος","stepTransliteration":"orgilos","gloss":"quick-tempered","_zh_tw_Gloss":"暴燥","_es_Gloss":"iracundo","_zh_Gloss":"暴燥"},{"strongNumber":"G3949","matchingForm":"παροργίζω","stepTransliteration":"parorgizō","gloss":"to anger","_zh_tw_Gloss":"怒氣","_es_Gloss":"enojar","_zh_Gloss":"怒气"},{"strongNumber":"G3950","matchingForm":"παροργισμός","stepTransliteration":"parorgismos","gloss":"anger","_zh_tw_Gloss":"含怒","_es_Gloss":"enojo","_zh_Gloss":"含怒"}],"shortDef":"wrath, anger, the feeling and expression of strong displeasure and hostility; this can range from petty human anger to the righteous anger of God toward sinful disobedience","mediumDef":"wrath, anger, the feeling and expression of strong displeasure and hostility; this can range from petty human anger to the righteous anger of God toward sinful disobedience <br /><i>primarily</i> <b>mental bent, impulse; anger, indignation, wrath,</b> <ref='Eph.4.31'>Eph. 4:31;</ref> <ref='Col.3.8'>Col. 3:8;</ref> <greek>μετ᾽ ὀργῆς</greek>, <b>indignantly,</b> <ref='Mrk.3.5'>Mk. 3:5</ref>; <b>vengeance, punishment,</b> <ref='Mat.3.7'>Mt. 3:7</ref>; <ref='Luk.3.7; 21:23'>Lk. 3:7; 21:23</ref>; <ref='Rom.13.4'>Rom. 13:4</ref>, 5","stepGloss":"wrath","stepTransliteration":"orgē","count":36,"_es_Definition":"ira, cólera ; retribución, castigo ; venganza","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) (情緒層面) 憤怒<br>2) (報復層面) 怒氣<br> 2a) 對曠野的以色列民的審判<br> 2b) 神未來的審判","_zh_Definition":"1) (情绪层面) 愤怒<br>2) (报复层面) 怒气<br> 2a) 对旷野的以色列民的审判<br> 2b) 神未来的审判","_step_Typ